OneWireViewer-Linux — licensing & provenance
=============================================

This repository bundles code from more than one upstream source. Nothing here
was written from scratch except the build/install scripts and documentation,
which are released into the public domain (CC0 / do-as-you-wish).

1. OneWireAPI (lib/OneWireAPI.jar) and OneWireViewer (src/onewireviewer/**,
   prebuilt/OneWireViewer.jar)
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Copyright (C) Dallas Semiconductor Corporation (later Maxim Integrated,
   now Analog Devices). Distributed under the MIT-style "Dallas Semiconductor"
   license reproduced below.

2. PDKAdapterUSB — the DS9490R USB bridge (src/pdkadapterusb/**)
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------
   The libusb DS2490 driver + JNI shim derive from the Maxim "1-Wire Public
   Domain Kit" (PDK). Recovered from a public 2005 mirror
   (http://globalreset.org/files/distribution/PDKAdapterUSB.tar.gz) because the
   official OneWireViewer-Linux.zip is no longer distributed. The PDK carries
   the same MIT-style Dallas Semiconductor license.

